textBeforeTable: Reporting Groups This study was comprised of a Screening Period (up to 2 weeks), a Run-in Period (4 weeks), a Treatment Period (TP: 17 weeks), and a Follow-up (8 weeks) Period. The TP had a Single-dose Phase (Bioequivalence [BE] Phase: 28 days) and a 12-week Multiple-dose Phase. In the BE Phase, 186 participants were randomized; 167 received >=1 treatment dose.
